div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington. Northern Division.
In the matter of the application of Arthur B. Martin for Writ of Habeas Corpus. } No. 2852 Order
On reading the above Affidavit and being fully advised in the premises:

It Is Hereby Ordered That the papers and pleadings in the above entitled cause be filed by the Clerk and served by the Marshal and that all steps be taken hrein without the payment of costs in advance, and without the petitioner ebing required to give security for the same.
In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington
In the matter of the application of Arthur B. Martin for Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, Northern Division Sep 24 1914 Frank L Crosby, Clerk. By EML Deputy
